			<ns0:name>elijahtaylor@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/elijahtaylor@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Stdout is fully buffered by default, so on untrusted crashes we can lose up to 8K of debug/info output.  Since printf debugging is so important currently for NaCl, this really hinders debugging.

A workaround involves a call to setvbuf to override this behavior, or to use stderr to output debug info, but many developers are used to default line-buffering for stdout in ordinary console apps.

It is also inconsistent with our newlib port which either maintains a much smaller buffer, or line buffers output.

